		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV>Adjustments to poison based agro = I can use my DoTs a bit more freely = good</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Smoothing spell progression 1-50 = nice</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Hybrids need a new /disc or 2 !&nbsp; And then 'smooth' those out across 1-50 by adding 1 or 2 weaker versions of each</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Clicking off buffs = YAY</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Giving more solo options to everyone = good</DIV>
<DIV>BUT</DIV>
<DIV>Be careful - the cited warrior example is a disaster - sure it would help solo - but it also helps raiding, as the non tanking warriors can now boost their DPS - why not just pack along a ton of warriors for DPS and a huge supply of backup tanks.&nbsp; Its a zerglings dream.&nbsp; Far far better solution is - warrior can up their riposte chance a ton at the expense of agro - that also increases solo DPS and solo defence, but does nothing to increase raid DPS.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>A BL hard to resist slow - shamans and chanters are having kittens about this I bet - and the most common BL is already the Vah Shir.&nbsp; They better get one too.&nbsp; As much as I want a hard to resist slow - I just know this is a storm brewing.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Boosting healing = yay.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Stick a pet focus in DON = available.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>As said above - our pet heals need to be fast casting.&nbsp; Our pet heals need to be about as good as what clerics can do for PCs - it always used to be prior to lvl 60 (except for CH)&nbsp; </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>An idea - put in a line of pet and lord heals, spells that heal both in one quick cast.&nbsp; These spells would be useful for dealing with AE.&nbsp; The existing line of self only, and of pet only heals would be good for tank soloing and pet soloing respectively. (if the pet heals are given more appropriate cast times)</DIV>
