		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			some things you should keep in mind with those changes which in general I find good but not going too far.<br><br>- beastlords fight in melee range and frequently work as tank, they get rampaged on when theres AE rampage you cant avoid, they get to off tank mobs sometimes etc. This results in a few things<br>  - all our spells give us way more aggro then others. We dont have a big nuke and its 30sec cast time so a lot use a few nukes which gets us more aggro then the equivalent dmg done by a wizie for example without any lowering aggro AA. Added to that, were in melee range so it increases aggro further<br>  - you put mage and necro pet heals on same line as us but difference is they will be out of melee range of mob and rarely tanking. So while they can channel a 9sec heal on pet, we cant. We need a specific line of pet heals that are thoughtful of our melee. Anything above 2 cast time is gonna be a big prob in high end raiding and is one of the problems a lot of bst dont even use pets on raid because they die way too fast. Also a lot of high end mobs have a stun in 1 of their many AE which would interupt any long cast time heals.<br><br>              thus : think about both Pet heals for a melee class and Aggro for a melee class<br><br>- ability to buff. We can work as slower but we also work as buffer when take shammy role. We dont want to be on par with them for buffs we just want the hasle of single buff casting to go away. Give us group focus of alladnu, group IoS (though barely noone asks for IoS since they are maxed stats in high end game), give us a group haste or at least a longer lasting one. Casting haste every 12min in adition to focus, SA,SV, slowing, helping on heals sometimes, keeping pet up, taking care not to get aggro on mob / enrage / etc, taking care of Keeping aggro sometimes is a lot to do. You seem to have given us a low duration on nearly every spell.<br>Beastlord just have a hell of a time when they reach high end to keep up all those spells. Keeping your item buffs (for example 8th ring, quarm earring), haste on whole group, SA on whole raid, Paragon, New don buff, epic (got better but it still has to be clicked frequently) etc is a real pain if you want to concentrate on your job and not only keeping your buffs and those of your group / raid up.<br><br>- DPS, you still didnt touch the dps problem at high end. Big thread was posted on the problems we have in high end as a DPS class. You say we get a lot of strength in our pet but necro and mage pet are WAY stronger when I compare them on high end mobs where the procs are resisted so much. You would say that our pet can stun and snare and can be imbued in all sort of resist but thats no good. Our pet CANT stun at high end, 90% of mob I fight resist it or are immune to stun. Our pet CANT snare mobs, hobble now stacks but it cant even snare correctly a green sebilis froglok. Our pet CANT be imbued in different resist spell while keeping up on dps, the gap in dmg between our desease / poison / fire / cold and magic procs is just too big to switch.<br><br>Now lets take our top 10 list :<br><br>1) Beastlord slowing: OK<br>2) Beastlord sustained dps: not touched<br>3) Beastlord "burst" dps: not much done to it, DoN helps sort of but not by any significant margin<br>4) Beastlord aggro issues:<br>  - poison dot : OK<br>  - other types of aggro : not touched (DD, weapon procs, added to slow)<br>5) Spell casting reinforcement mastery (SCRM) : not touched<br>6) Ferocity of Irionu : not touched<br>7) Add a group version of Infusion of spirit : not touched<br>8) Pet buff box: OK<br>9) Omens utility issues:<br>  - focus of alladnu : not touched<br>  - SA : not touched<br>  - spiritual line : not touched<br>10) Beastlord pet heals : talk about it but nothing specific
								<p><div style="width: 100%; height: 120; overflow: hidden;">
								
