	<tr>
	
		<td class="msg_user_cell" width="150" valign=top>
		
			 









<a href='/eq/view_profile?user.id=31049'  class="auth_text"  style="font-weight:bold;" >	
<span style='color:#CC0099;'>Iskandos</span></a>
			<br>
			
			<span style="font-size: 8pt;">
			Lorekeeper<br>
			
				Posts: 83<br>
				
				Registered: 05-05-2004
				
			</span>
			


			
			<br>
			
				<img src="/i/p.gif" height=8 width=150 border=0 alt=""><br>
				
			<a href='/eq/view_profile?user.id=31049'>







<img src="/eq/i/icons/Classes/beastlord.gif" border=0 alt=""/></a><br>
			


			
			<p>
			






<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=beastlordbalance&message.id=2326#M2326">10</a> of 118
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 1998 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV>Pet heal&nbsp;as it is now is semi-useless (speaking as a level 70 Beastlord)... if you are solo and facing a lone mob or two weak/slow mobs, pet heals are great!... if you have multiple mid-to-strong adds while soloing, and the pet is off-tanking one, there is a good chance the mob/mobs hitting you will interrupt you before the heal can go off (nine seconds is a really long time to be standing there casting)... if you're in a group/raid situation where your pet is going down fast from an ae/dot/ramp/whatever, you will most likely not get a heal off in time to save it -- if you do, you will need to cast it again to get the warder up enough in health to make it viable for a few more rounds, when you will need to do it all over again. All that pet healing = mucho lost dps, which is the main reason you're in that group/raid to begin with. Pet Affinity helps in this regard, as it lets the warder take group and MGB heals, but many Beastlords are unable/unwilling to pay the high AA cost (12 AA I believe it is now) to get it&nbsp;-- and with the odd pathing warders sometimes take, there will be times when they are not in range of those group heals. Personally, the new Growl of the Panther spell is more useful as a pet heal to me than Healing of Mikkily because of the 3 second cast time vs the 9 seconds on the pet heal (not to mention the hp boost and damage mod, all for about 120 mana more per cast -- I loose 1k of pet healing but gain everything else...).</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Another idea for improved pet heals:&nbsp;add some&nbsp;insta or near-insta (1-2 seconds) cast Heal Over Time spells with a fast duration that land automatically on the warder without swapping your target (ie: a Mikkily alternative could be 275/tick for 10 ticks, or 450/tick for&nbsp;6 ticks, or 680/tick for 4 ticks, etc -- any of which would equal the current 2730 base heal -- these could be some of the alternate level spells you mention adding... get a single heal at one level and a few levels later get the fast-cast HoT version). The warder could then receive the benefits of a pet heal (need to make sure it's stackable with other HoT/regen effects, however -- ie, Pious Elixir, Pious Cleansing, Spiritual Serenity, Spirit of the Wood, or even our own Paragon, Feral Vigor and Growl spells) without pulling the Beastlord from melee for any noticeable amount of time -- we are primarily a melee dps class, after all. If each tick could be counted as a separate heal by the game engine, they would further benefit from our Healing Adept/Mastery AA lines, which would be most excellent!&nbsp; I don't ask for much, do I? <img src='/i/smilies/16x16_smiley-tongue.gif' width=16 height=16 border=0></DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Pets on raids... letting us make them even smaller would be very&nbsp;nice <img src='/i/smilies/16x16_smiley-happy.gif' width=16 height=16 border=0>&nbsp; Form a 64-player raid and hit those wonderfully small halls of Txevu... then add 15-20 pets/flappies... typical clearing pulls will be 2-4 mobs... now play "where is the Main Assist's&nbsp;target ring?" -- it's a game that usually ends when the Raid Leader says "Pocket the @#$% pets!!" <img src='/i/smilies/16x16_smiley-surprised.gif' width=16 height=16 border=0>&nbsp; A fully shrunken Vah Shir with a fully shrunken level 70 warder has the same size ratio as an unshrunken Vah Shir and an unshrunken level 70 warder (about shoulder height, either way)... it would be nice if the warder could be hit with Tiny Companion two or three more times, giving it the size ratio of a level&nbsp;9 warder when compared to a fully shrunken player (or, in basic terms, make it under knee high when both you and the warder are fully shrunken)&nbsp; I rather like having a huge honkin tiger next to me when I solo -- and it has it's uses in some group/raid situations, too -- but we need to have a greater control over the size of them when a huge honkin&nbsp;warder&nbsp;just doesn't work well with others.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Pet spam would also be nice to get rid of on a raid. If it can tell me and only me that a target is invalid, why does it have to tell everyone in earshot that it's calming down and awaiting orders?&nbsp; Add multiple Beastlords, Mages, and Necros, and you have a real spamfest. I'm assuming there's no filter to turn off pet-proc spam too, as I've fielded the "how do I turn off your warder's spell spam" /tell quite a few times <img src='/i/smilies/16x16_smiley-wink.gif' width=16 height=16 border=0></DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Suxbst makes a good point about the scalability of pet focii... the level 70 warder, Spirit of Rashara, hits for 91 max without focus or the Growl of the Beast haste/damage mod, and scales up to 99 max with Minion of Eternity (and no haste)&nbsp;(with GotB haste, it's is 94 unfocussed and 102 with MoE or 105 with Ritual Summoning). Though the improvement is nice, it's not something that makes&nbsp;most Beastlords go "OMG! OMG!&nbsp;WOW!" -- the improvement primarily comes from the pet haste spell, and not the pet focus itself. Minion of Eternity is probably the best a casual-raiding Beastlord could get at this time.&nbsp;The same can be seen with&nbsp;the 64 warder, Spirit of Sorsha, which hits for 77 base unbuffed, and scales up to 86 base unbuffed with Minion of Eternity -- reportedly, Ritual Summoning also caps it out at 86. It seems the higher the warder, the less benefit a focus gives us... and the higher the focus, the less benefit it gives as well... overall,&nbsp;this seems to be a rather steep curve of diminishing returns -- perhaps it could be looked at, to see if the scaling could be improved somewhat? Receiving better results from focii&nbsp;would be something that would benefit all pet classes, as well.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>And what about some group buffin? I'm guessing a Dev never played a Beastlord on a full raid where no Shamen showed up (or&nbsp;a long-lasting&nbsp;exp&nbsp;group with&nbsp;five melee dps and one healer)&nbsp;<img src='/i/smilies/16x16_smiley-very-happy.gif' width=16 height=16 border=0>&nbsp; Some group versions of haste, IoS, and Alladnu (or even a combo IoS/Alladnu group spell) sure would be handy.&nbsp;And there's also&nbsp;tweaking Perfection of Spirit back up to what it was in Beta (Paragon gives 1200 hp/480 mana... Perfection1 gives 1332 hp/540 mana --&nbsp;is 132 hp and 60 mana every 15 minutes for&nbsp;3 AA really considered an improvement? And for&nbsp;6 AA more you can get Perfection3, which gives 1602hp/660 mana...&nbsp;9 AA total to gain 402 hp and 180 mana every 15 minutes)... or making Ferocity of Irionu more of an actual upgrade to Ferocity... or bumping Spiritual Ascendance/Dominion up in duration enough to meet our MGB timers... or tweaking the range of Feral Swipe to better match melee range so we don't have to go directly under large mobs like Quarm to be in range, while our melee range extends considerably further out... personally, I would think that these existing&nbsp;spell/AA issues would be of more importance than boosting our healing ability. Don't get me wrong -- I love heals, we wouldn't live too long without em... but Beastlords aren't exactly invited to groups because of their supreme healing abilities <img src='/i/smilies/16x16_smiley-wink.gif' width=16 height=16 border=0></DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Overall, the changes sound very nice, though I imagine everyone will have their own take on what should or shouldn't be included <img src='/i/smilies/16x16_smiley-happy.gif' width=16 height=16 border=0></DIV>
								<p><div style="width: 100%; height: 120; overflow: hidden;">
								
							<DIV><span></span><br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=483674&amp;resize=true" target="_blank">Iskandar Darkpaw</a>, Wildcaller of Shar Vahl<br><a href="http://www.cohort.ws/" target="_blank">Cohort Chalybeius</a>, Cazic Thule server
							</div>
								
		</td></tr>
