			>
			<blockquote><hr>Beastlords<br><br>We will add at least one new slow spell for you which has an innate resistance mod built in so that it lands more often.  This will help you perform the role of slower in your groups, since you don't have access to the powerful resistance lowering spells of other slowing classes.<br></blockquote><hr><br><br>This is good news .. but honestly I've never had TOO much of a problem slowing .. the exceptions seem to be PoEarth, which has insanely excessive<br>resist rates, and perhaps some of the higher mobs in MPG .. but its really not too bad there. <br><br>Score = 8<br><br><br><blockquote><hr>We will be boosting your healing so it stays on par with ranger healing when we improve ranger heals.<br></blockquote><hr><br><br>I dont even have all of my Omen's healing AA's done yet, getting there .. but even so with IH5 foci and a majority of my healing aa's .. single target heal will land for about 900, and crit for nearly 2K.  Pet heals i land for about 3500 non crit.  Hastended mending same way and I dont even have all of the ranks of that yet either, and I can reuse it every 9 min.<br><br>So you want me to be able to heal better ... okaaaay ... *shuts up*<br><br>Score = 5<br><br><br><blockquote><hr>We want to assure pet classes that we believe you should be able to use their pets in most gameplay situations, including raids.  We believe that pet classes do not have many problems with pets on raids at the moment, but want you to understand that we intend for you to use pets on raids and if you find that there is a problem, we will find ways to correct it.<br></blockquote><hr><br><br>I dont have a problem with pets on raids .. except maybe that they arent smart enough to stay at precicely max-melee range on mobs that AE rampage .. I'd like to see THAT fixed.<br><br>Score = Need more information<br><br><br><blockquote><hr>We will be increasing the availability of pet focus items, particularly for the more casual players.<br></blockquote><hr><br><br>Casual players dont need it.  And I've been busting my arse making raids and saving LAP / DKP for when a MoE foci drops .. dont cheapen my work please.<br><br>Score = 3<br><br><br><blockquote><hr>We will be looking into the casting time of some of your pet healing spells and reducing the casting time where appropriate.<br></blockquote><hr><br><br>The actual pet heal spell DOES need this.  10 second cast time and with foci reduced to maybe 8 seconds.  I know, I know, you are thinking well CH is the same way .. but the dps of newer expansion mobs is pretty high, and ive generally got a lot of mana to burn, and i need to be able to save my pet a little bit easier.  5-6 or less seconds would be great.<br><br>Score = 10<br><br>Buffing .. I really dont want to be a buffer.  I hate buffing groups and more importantly I hate buffing raids even more.  I dont mind buffing SA, nor SV .. but what really gets my goat is buffing IoS, Allandu, Haste, Sow .. you got 2 choices as far as im concerned, either make them self and pet only so i got an excuse as to WHY I cant spend 5 minutes buffing every single single target buff on people or give us group versions of these spells to make buffing less painless.<br><br>Debuffing .. dont care.  Unless you were to give us a Malo . .which would help solve the slow problem too.<br><br>Clicking off pet buffs .. great .. but how are you going to implement that when you can only see 4 buff icons at once?<br><br>The DoN spells were really nice, I've actually replaced Fero with them in most of my standard spell templates.  And I've learned to work with  the limitations that having casting the spell target your pet brings, BUT .. what would really be nice, if possible, would be for it to not lose its current target and still buff the pet / master .. however I can see how there might be some coding limitations with this.<br><br>Hmm .. other than that .. you know those nifty lifetap augs that I personally am heavily addicted to?  Like the veintappers stone?  I'd *die* for mana tap augments to be placed in the game.<br><br>Other than that .. great work .. I love my beastlord .. hes the best class in the game, by FAR.
