<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=beastlordbalance&message.id=2334#M2334">16</a> of 118
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 1919 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV></DIV>
<DIV>Honestly??</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>We beastlords are about to get shafted.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><STRONG>Poison dot line..</STRONG></DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Speaking for myself only, I actually try to generate agro.&nbsp; i purposely walk that fine line between ping-pong and next on the list.&nbsp;&nbsp; Many times, my poison dots have generated JUST enough agro to keep the mobs from mauling the clerics and casters.&nbsp; I have saved MANY raids this way.&nbsp; I have saved many groups this way.&nbsp; This is the way I play.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>I am aware that MANY Beastlords see our agro as a crutch to our dps.&nbsp; I see it as a huge boon.&nbsp; A good beast knows his limits as far agro goes.&nbsp; A good beast knows when to watch for mobs to maul the clerics/casters.&nbsp; A GREAT beast wouldn't have to worry much about it because of our ability to maintain good agro, and keep it.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Taking away, or lessening, the agro from our poison dots will undoubtedly also take away our ability to save groups and raids.&nbsp; </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><STRONG>Slows...</STRONG></DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>I&nbsp;have actually had conversations with shaman about this change.&nbsp; Most seem happy about it.&nbsp; Lessening our resist rate (not that I have much issue myself - 'cept in mpg/rss) is not all that overpowering by comparison of the mobs we are fighting when we ARE the main slower.&nbsp; Lets face it, not many folks would take a Beast as a slower to RSS routinely.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>I don't see&nbsp;a Beastlord replacing a shaman at any time.&nbsp; Allowing us to slow better only helps free the shamans from their pigeon holes.&nbsp; </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><STRONG>Buffs...</STRONG></DIV>
<DIV><STRONG></STRONG>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Oh for the love of money, give us some group buffs.&nbsp; Our Talisman Line and Haste line are god aweful on mana when grouping.&nbsp; Give us group veresions of these spells, cost it out at buffing 5 people if you have to, but keep the same length (atleast make&nbsp;haste last longer!!).&nbsp; The time involved and the mana involved when casting on all 6 people in a group (not to mention stat buffs - IOS anyone?) is insane.&nbsp; The only group buffs we get are our SV and SA line.&nbsp; Throw us a bone.&nbsp; Please.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><STRONG>Heals...</STRONG></DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>I would like to thank you in advance.&nbsp; Our current heals are subpar for our lvl of play.&nbsp; Again, without trying to become the next shaman, we did need an upgrade.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><STRONG>Pet Heals...</STRONG></DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>I do believe the heals themselves are fine as they are, with regard to the healing power.&nbsp; However, the cast time involved is a little too much.&nbsp; Shorten it by a second or 2, and go from there.&nbsp; The last thing&nbsp;I want is to be know as the pet cleric class.&nbsp; I think the mana cost for pet heals is proper also.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><STRONG>Pet buffs...</STRONG></DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Is it too much to ask that the proc's from pets be shown?&nbsp;&nbsp; Alot of folks are huge on their own personal DPS.&nbsp; Make it shown to owner only if needed, but allow us the ability to truely parse our DPS.&nbsp; Folks keep saying that our DPS is in line with the other classes, yet we cannot SEE the numbers to prove it.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>I do feel the mana cost / timer on buffs are well balanced.&nbsp; Atleast&nbsp;I am not buffing my pet every other fight.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Thanks for you thoughts.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Zartuim Agromonster - 70 Beastlord</DIV>
<DIV>Impudent Blasphemy - 66 Cleric - Semi-Retired</DIV>	
		</td></tr>
