		" 
			>
			<DIV>Essant_LeFur</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>To see more than 4 pet buff icons - grab the left/right side of the pet buff window, and drag it bigger - job done.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>On to BL heals.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>I been thinking about this - and here is what *I* want to see.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Fast casting mana efficient heals that I can target as required</DIV>
<DIV>Fast casting big figure pet only heals</DIV>
<DIV>Very mana efficient Heals over Time ala mini-torpor</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>And the big one - the new one - the controversial one</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>A 'defensive proc' buff that, when you get hit, casts a modest heal onto you, that expires after about 12 seconds.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Huh?&nbsp; where did that come from?&nbsp; From the shaman 're envisioning' actually - the Devs are looking for a way to balance shaman healing against their slowing ability, and naturally our healing ability must logically have the same issue.&nbsp; Chanters dont heal so the other slowing class isnt affected.&nbsp; Basically, SoE needs a heal that isnt amplified by the benefit of slow, and this 'reactive' heal (as robbed shamelessly from EQ2) is it.&nbsp; If a mob is unslowed, the reactive heal puts out a LOT more healing, because the mob will get in 4-6 attack rounds of singles-quad hits.&nbsp; If the mob is slowed however (and not mitigated) then the mob will get in 2-3.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Anyway - on to numbers.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Lets use the current OoW heal as a baseline.&nbsp; 680 damage for 245 mana in 3 seconds cast 2.25 recast.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Thats fast casting, and reasonably mana efficient.&nbsp; I'll leave where I think it needs to be for a bit</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Pet heals - these need to be in the same scale as cleric&nbsp;'light' spells&nbsp;to be honest.&nbsp; That means the top pet heal is 3770 health for 740 mana in 3.75 seconds or there abouts - pet only</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>I really also think that pet only HoT equivalent to shaman torpor is not inappropriate.&nbsp; That means top of the line pet HoT is 820 per tick for 4 ticks for 520 mana with 6 second cast time - again pet only</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>I would like to see a 'mini torpor' type HoT - but - the Growl spells we got in DoN are kind of already this.&nbsp; kind of.&nbsp; Be nice to have a targetable version that was just the healing, with a much lower mana cost.&nbsp; but anyway.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>And the reactive heal?&nbsp; OK so it needs to heal twice as much as a base direct heal for the same mana cost, because on average half the healing might very well be wasted.&nbsp; And it also needs to heal a little bit more again because the healing is spread over time, and that is suppoed to be more efficient.&nbsp; And finally lets make it a tad bigger in general than the direct heal for differentiation purposes.&nbsp; So - the top range reactive heal should aim to have a maximum heal possibility of 1500 for 285 mana with a 3 second cast time.&nbsp; Give it a 2.25 second recast time because you couldnt 'stack it' anyway and you can chain a direct heal.&nbsp; Its duration is 12 seconds.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Now - an unslowed enemy from original era would get 4-5 attacks in that time - but in places like OoW where their base delay is a lot lower, thats 8-9.&nbsp; Lets use 7 attack sets in 12 seconds.&nbsp; By far the most common hit is a double, but triples and quads are also fairly common.&nbsp; I am going to use a tad under 3 attacks average per attack set - so that the average expected number of hits in 12 seconds is 20.&nbsp; Half of these are going to miss or be blocked or what ever, so my final 'guess' is 10.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>A fully slowed enemy from a shaman will have a quarter of this, 2.5 hits.&nbsp; A partly mitigated slow from a BL is probably around half, or 5 hits in 12 seconds.&nbsp; Most high end trash mobs will fit this category, so lets use that as our baseline.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>5 hits = 5 reactions from our heal, meaning each reaction has to be around 300.&nbsp; Now in 12 seconds, I have managed to be missed by every singe attack, and I have managed to be hit by every singe attack, so the potential is there for some HUGE variety.&nbsp; Remember we needed to cap the amount of healing this thing can do to 1500, so lets put in a cap on how many hits the heal can react to.&nbsp; 5 hits and it fades - now we can not exceed our initial premise of 1500 healing which predicated on the idea that it could be that high only because there was also a chance for wasting some or all of it</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Ahh - potential exploit, multiple enemies, and we had a 2.25 sec recast.&nbsp; Now the power is chainable, and thats no good.&nbsp; So the recast needs to be 12 seconds after all.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>So - my new spell idea is - for 285 mana, you put a defensive proc on your target, that heals for 300 when activated, that fades after&nbsp;5 activations or 12 seconds.&nbsp; Its based on thought experiment only, and tuned around the idea that you will typically be slowing with your best slow, and having it mitigated somewhat.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Anyway - thats all based on where BL healing is at now.&nbsp; How much does SoE think it has to change by?</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Personally - I think rangers should be getting heals in the 1k range, for 3 sec cast and not terribly mana efficient.&nbsp; And I think that our heals should stay at the range they are, and these 'alternative' heal over time/reactive heals should make the buffer between their ability and ours.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Entirely my opinion, which means none of it is false.&nbsp; May not be appropriate for EQ of course, but at least you cant try to tell me that it isnt my opinion :&nbsp; neener neener.</DIV>	
		</td></tr>
		<tr>
		
		<td class="msg_date_cell" valign=bottom nowrap>
		<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
		 <span class=date_text>03-15-2005</span> <span class=time_text>05:19 PM</span>
		</span>
		</td>

		
