			Great start.  I dont see any self-only buffs mentioned and the idea of a BL HoT seems to have gone out the window.  So how about a self only HoT? would help with the solo end of the game and not really do much to offset raid/grouping balance as more powerfull HoT's would be available. As it stands with a shaman HoT 820/tik and pally 585/tik I think a self only 200-300/tik spell would make solo'ing for exp/AA at lot less stressfull.<br>(not compairing BL to clerics as they neither slow or are a hybred)<br><br>Other self-buffs? A combination of SV aladnu IoS Haste would be neat.<br><br>Sinse monks were pretty much given our nuke line ( 800 dd /30s recast/61 1200dd@69 ) and their version as far as I recall is unresistable how about allowing us to change what our nuke is checked against resistance wise, somewhat like how we have pet proc buffs of every resist ( now lacking usefullnes though ) <br><br>great start Devs, lacking feedback on BL DPS issues though<br><br>Grats monks on mitagation back, and DPS ability<br>Grats wizies on MB being looked at, that nerf was WAY to harsh considering SK's can now do the same thing with HT that got MB nerfed.	
